                            <comment id="16376112" author="githubbot" created="Sun, 25 Feb 2018 15:10:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;GitHub user mcoolive opened a pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/logging-log4j2/pull/153&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/logging-log4j2/pull/153&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-2270&quot; title=&quot;Strings::join, when called with [null] returns &amp;quot;null&amp;quot; instead of EMPTY&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LOG4J2-2270&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LOG4J2-2270&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Strings::join(&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;null&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;) should return EMPTY&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The javadoc of Strings::join states: &apos;Null objects or empty strings&lt;br/&gt;
    within the iteration are represented by empty strings&apos;.&lt;br/&gt;
    But when call with an array of one element that is null, it returns&lt;br/&gt;
    &quot;null&quot;, where I expect EMPTY (&quot;&quot;).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Add unit tests on Strings::join. One would fail without the change&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


